paper_metadata.extraction_summary: Extracted BRCA2 variant information, including penetrance data and individual records.

variants.additional_notes: This mutation has been described as benign in studies of breast and ovarian cancers.
key_quotes: The missense mutation c.7397T>C (p.Val2466Ala), was the most common mutation and was observed in 78 patients (74.3%).
Studies of breast and ovarian cancers have described this mutation as benign, and its clinical significance remains unknown.

patients.phenotype: associated with an elevated risk of overall cancer

functional_data.summary: This mutation has been associated with an elevated risk of overall cancer in predominantly Caucasian and African cohorts.

variants.additional_notes: This mutation is the only recognized common non-synonymous polymorphism in the BRCA2 gene.
key_quotes: The second most common BRCA2 mutation in this cohort was the BRCA2 N372H non-conservative amino acid substitution polymorphism.
This mutation has been associated with an elevated risk of overall cancer in predominantly Caucasian and African cohorts.
